主题: <strong>异种武器弹药</strong><br>
作者: <strong>折剑者绯月</strong> 于 <strong>2017-03-23, 周四 19:49:37</strong>
<dd class="postbody">
<span style="font-size: 14pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>异种武器弹药</strong></span><br><br><table class="bbc_table"><tr><td><strong>物品名称</strong>　　　　<td><strong>价格</strong>　<td><strong>重量（磅）</strong><td><strong>出处</strong></tr><tr><td>连发弩矢（5）<td>1GP<td>1<td>CRB</tr><tr><td>小星星石（10）<td>5CP<td>2<td>Halflings</tr><tr><td>尖角石弹丸（10）<td>1GP<td>5<td>Halflings</tr><tr><td>纤维石弹丸（10）<td>1SP<td>4<td>Halflings</tr><tr><td>海绵石弹丸（10）<td>10GP<td>2<td>Halflings</tr><tr><td>荆棘箭（20）<td>1GP<td>1<td>W1</tr></table><hr /><strong>连发弩矢 Repeating crossbow bolts</strong><br>连发弩矢被设计用于以连发弩发射。它们的售价略高于普通弩矢，并以5支一组出售而非10支（以和弹匣容量相匹配）<br><br><strong>小星星石 Little Starstones</strong><br>经管这些石头在工艺上可以认为是投石索弹药，但是这些织物包裹的鹅卵石主要是用于发信号或庆典而不是战斗，因为它们实在不足以让被击中的人感到疼痛。当浸入油或者高浓度酒精，它们会燃烧发光持续1轮，如同一支蜡烛一样照亮一片区域，并在飞行中划出一条光带。它们通常并不足够热而且燃烧得太快因此不能用于点燃可燃物。<br>这些石头用于攻击时只会造成1点钝击伤害。<br><div>Stone, Little Starstones<br>Though they are technically sling ammunition, these thread- or cloth-wrapped pebbles are mainly used for signaling or celebration rather than battle, as they barely hit hard enough to sting. When Spongeed in oil or strong alcohol, they burn brightly for 1 round, illuminating an area like a candle and creating brief streaks of light as they fly through the air. They generally aren’t hot enough and burn out too quickly to ignite combustibles.</div><strong>尖角石弹丸 Sharpstones Bullet</strong><br>一层薄薄的焙烧黏土复盖在尖角和锯齿状脊上并复盖在这个特制的弹丸上。熟练使用者知道如何打开这层黏土（自由动作）因此这个弹丸在射出去时暴露尖角或锯齿，并同时造成穿刺或挥砍伤害<br>小型生物使用其作为弹药时可以造成1D3点穿刺或挥砍伤害，中型生物使用其作为弹药时可以造成1D4点穿刺或挥砍伤害。<br><div>Bullet, Sharpstones<br>A thin layer of baked clay covers the spikes and jagged ridges covering this specially designed bullet. A proficient user knows how to crack the clay (a free action) so that it peels off from either the spikes or ridges when fired, dealing either piercing or slashing damage.</div><strong>纤维石弹丸 Softstones Bullet</strong><br>这些被弹性纤维包裹的石头被投石索发射时会造成非致命钝击伤害。<br><div>Bullet, Softstones<br>These tight bundles of elastic fibers deal nonlethal damage when fired from a sling.</div><strong>海绵石弹丸 Spongestones Bullet</strong><br>这些弹丸确实是由多孔的石头或者吸水后粉碎的重木制成。<br>海绵石弹丸通常被用来传递毒素或者燃烧的灯油。一瓶灯油可以浸染10发弹丸。当弹丸被点燃时（如果可以有火的话是一个自由动作），一枚燃烧的油性海绵石弹丸会造成钝击伤害和1D2火焰伤害，并且点燃可燃物（例如茅草顶棚）。海绵石可以在投石索里燃烧超过三轮才会令投石索变成破损状态。<br><div>Bullet, Spongestones<br>These bullets are actually made from a porous stone or heavy wood that absorbs liquids and shatters on impact.<br>Spongestones are often used to deliver poison or burning oil. A flask of oil completely saturates 10 Spongestones. When ignited (a free action if fire is available), a burning, oil-Spongeed Spongestone deals +1d2 fire damage and can ignite combustible materials (such as a thatched roof ). Allowing a Spongestone to burn in a sling’s cup for more than 1d3 rounds gives the sling the broken condition</div><strong>荆棘箭 Thorn</strong><br>这些箭矢镶嵌了玫瑰刺并且以漆玫瑰花瓣装点。此弹药用于荆棘弓。<br><div>Thorn: These small arrows are tipped with a wicked rose thorn and fletched with lacquered rose petals.</div>
